    <section id="policies">
        <h2 class="section-title">Course Policies</h2>
        <div class="row">
            <div class="col-md-6">
                <div class="policy-box shadow-sm">
                    <h5><i class="fas fa-user-check me-2"></i>Attendance</h5>
                    <ul class="small">
                        <li>27-29 classes: 60 pts</li>
                        <li>24-26 classes: 40 pts</li>
                        <li>20-23 classes: 20 pts</li>
                        <li>< 20 classes: 0 pts</li>
                    </ul>
                </div>
            </div>
            <div class="col-md-6">
                <div class="policy-box shadow-sm">
                    <h5><i class="fas fa-robot me-2"></i>AI Usage</h5>
                    <p class="small">AI permitted for minor brainstorming but requires "human in the loop." Plagiarism via AI = F (Zero pts). Be critical and interactive with AI tools.</p>
                </div>
            </div>
            <div class="col-md-12">
                <div class="policy-box shadow-sm">
                    <h5>Academic Integrity</h5>
                    <p class="small">NAU expects honesty, trustworthiness, and responsibility. Plagiarism includes using 3+ words in succession without citation. Review full policies at policy.nau.edu.</p>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
    </section>

    <section id="slo" class="bg-light p-4 rounded border">
        <h2 class="section-title">Learning Outcomes (SLO)</h2>
        <div class="row small overflow-auto" style="max-height: 400px;">
            <div class="col-12">
                <ol>
                    <li>Analyze critical issues of multicultural education in sociopolitical contexts (TESOL 2a, 2b, 2e).</li>
                    <li>Synthesize principles to plan for culturally relevant environments (TESOL 3a).</li>
                    <li>Describe influence of social/political identities (race, class, gender) on school policies.</li>
                    <li>Associate cross-cultural experiences by conducting interviews (TESOL 2d).</li>
                    <li>Analyze sociocultural narratives of diverse student backgrounds (TESOL 2c).</li>
                    <li>Review current research via written discussions.</li>
                    <li>Apply knowledge of political variables to English learning (TESOL 1b).</li>
                    <li>Understand learner variables in English acquisition.</li>
                    <li>Apply cultural values to ESL teaching.</li>
                    <li>Address effects of racism and stereotyping in ESL.</li>
                    <li>Use resources to learn student cultures.</li>
                    <li>Explore schooling success factors (religion, orientation, class).</li>
                    <li>Apply knowledge of U.S. immigration patterns.</li>
                    <li>Review case studies and student narratives.</li>
                    <li>Explore school climate and structural issues (safety, class size).</li>
                    <li>Explore inequities and productive resolutions.</li>
                    <li>Examine intergroup relations and theories of conflict.</li>
                    <li>Analyze identities that perpetuate inequality in school structures.</li>
                </ol>
            </div>
        </div>
    </section>

